ok_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Function `sieve_address_do_validate` in file sieve-address.c does dereference `error_r` \n```\n\tif ( address == NULL ) {\n\t\t*error_r = \"null address\";\n\t\treturn FALSE;\n\t}\n```\nand then later checks for it being NULL :\n```\n\t\tif ( error_r != NULL )\n\t\t\t*error_r = str_c(ctx.error);\n```\n\nSo either, there is a first null check missing\nOr the later ones are redundant\n\nThis function in called from `sieve_address_validate`\n\n## Impact\n\nIf it is a missing null check, the impact of a null pointer dereference is a crash of the application.\nIt the null checks are redundant, there is no security impact.\nSo I reported this here to be sure.","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eFunction \u003ccode\u003esieve_address_do_validate\u003c/code\u003e in file sieve-address.c does dereference \u003ccode\u003eerror_r\u003c/code\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cpre class=\"highlight plaintext\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e    if ( address == NULL ) {\n        *error_r = \u0026quot;null address\u0026quot;;\n        return FALSE;\n    }\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand then later checks for it being NULL :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cpre class=\"highlight plaintext\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e        if ( error_r != NULL )\n            *error_r = str_c(ctx.error);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo either, there is a first null check missing\u003cbr\u003e\nOr the later ones are redundant\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis function in called from \u003ccode\u003esieve_address_validate\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"impact\"\u003eImpact\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf it is a missing null check, the impact of a null pointer dereference is a crash of the application.\u003cbr\u003e\nIt the null checks are redundant, there is no security impact.\u003cbr\u003e\nSo